solution:
$95 \% \mathrm{H}_2 \mathrm{SO}_4$ by weight means $100 \mathrm{~g} \mathrm{H}_2 \mathrm{SO}_4$ solution contains $95 \mathrm{~g} \mathrm{H}_2 \mathrm{SO}_4$ by mass. Molar mass of $\mathrm{H}_2 \mathrm{SO}_4=98 \mathrm{~g} \mathrm{~mol}^{-1}$
Moles in $95 \mathrm{~g}=\frac{95}{98}=0.969$ mole
Volume of $100 \mathrm{~g} \mathrm{H}_2 \mathrm{SO}_4$
$$
\begin{aligned}
& =\frac{\text { mass }}{\text { density }}=\frac{100 \mathrm{~g}}{1.834 \mathrm{~g} \mathrm{~cm}^{-3}} \\
& =54.52 \mathrm{~cm}^3=54.52 \times 10^{-3} \mathrm{~L}
\end{aligned}
$$
$$
\begin{aligned}
\text { Molarity } & =\frac{\text { Moles of solute }}{\text { Volme of solute in } \mathrm{L}} \\
& =\frac{0.969}{54.52 \times 10^{-3}}=17.8 \mathrm{M}
\end{aligned}
$$
